{"title_page": "Economic and Technological Development Zones", "text_new": "{{Infobox Chinese\n|order = st\n|s = {{linktext|\u56fd\u5bb6|\u7ea7|\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a}}\n|t = \u570b\u5bb6\u7d1a\u7d93\u6fdf\u6280\u8853\u958b\u767c\u5340\n|p = Gu\u00f3ji\u0101j\u00ed J\u012bngj\u00ec J\u00ecsh\u00f9 K\u0101if\u0101 Q\u016b\n}}\n\nThe '''National Economic and Technological Development Zones''' ({{zh|s={{linktext|\u56fd\u5bb6|\u7ea7|\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a}}|t=\u570b\u5bb6\u7d1a\u7d93\u6fdf\u6280\u8853\u958b\u767c\u5340|p=Gu\u00f3ji\u0101j\u00ed J\u012bngj\u00ec J\u00ecsh\u00f9 K\u0101if\u0101 Q\u016b}}) are the special areas of the [[China|People's Republic of China]] where [[foreign direct investment]] is encouraged.  They are usually called the \"Economic and Technological Development Zones\" or simply the \"Development Zones\".\n\nThese national level programs started with the [[special economic zones of China|Special Economic Zones]] for three cities in 1978, as part of [[Chinese economic reform|China's economic reform]], and were extended to the Economic and Technological Development Zones in 14 cities in 1984.\n\nThere are also pros and cons on development on these economic zones, the pros are creating more job opportunities, increasing its economic growth (national GDP) and encourage on foreign direct investment. As a result, it was a success because China is currently one of the fastest growing countries and significantly influencing the global economy. From the past two decades, China has become an industrialized country because of the development of these economic zones. In which encourage foreign direct investments, where trading, exports of manufacture goods, became one of the main aspect of economic growth. On the other hand, it also made it reliant  on these foreign investment, such as reliant on Hong Kong for these foreign investment, due to the reason that Hong Kong is a free trade market. Based on the case in Shenzhen, its problem with being one of the economic zones can be categorized in four category 1) Foreign exchange leakage,2) Cost ineffectiveness, 3) Failure to achieve state objectives and 4) Economic crimes and related social problems.[https://web.archive.org/web/20161220025544/http://www.ide.go.jp/English/Publish/Periodicals/De/pdf/87_01_05.pdf]\n\nChina has been among the top targets of global investment for more than two decades.   In the new age of [[global recession]], China keeps a stable [[Economic growth|growth rate]], thanks to the inexpensive labor, stable government, preferable [[tax rate]] and government's support to [[foreign direct investment|foreign investment]].\n\n==List of zones==\nIn 2006, there are now 49 Development Zones (in the order of the list in the [[:zh:\u56fd\u5bb6\u7ea7\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a|Chinese Wikipedia page]], i.e. in the order of the approvals):\n\n* [[Dalian Development Area]]\n* [[Haining]]\n* [[Qinhuangdao]]\n* [[Tianjin Economic-Technological Development Area]]\n* [[Yantai]]\n* [[Qingdao]]\n* [[Nantong]]\n* [[Lianyungang]]\n* [[Weihai]]\n* [[Fuqing]] Rongqiao\n* [[Tongshan County, Hubei|Tongshan]]\n* [[Shenyang]]\n* [[Harbin]]\n* [[Changchun]]\n* [[Wuhan]]\n* [[Wuhu City|Wuhu]]\n* [[Huizhou]] Dayawan\n* [[Beijing]]\n* [[Urumuqi]]\n* [[Hefei]]\n* [[Zhengzhou]]\n* [[Xi'an]]\n* [[Chengdu]]\n* [[Kunming]]\n* [[Changsha Economic and Technological Development Zone]]\n* [[Guiyang]]\n* [[Nanchang]]\n* [[Hohhot]]\n* [[Yinchuan]]\n* [[Nanjing]]\n* [[Suzhou Industrial Park]]\n* [[Shanghai]] Minhang\n* [[Shanghai]] Hongqiao\n* [[Caohejing Development Zone (Shanghai Metro)|Shanghai Caohejing Development Zone (Shanghai Metro)]]\n* [[Shanghai]] [[Pudong]] [[Lujiazui|Lujiazui Financial & Trading Zone]]\n* [[Shanghai]] [[Pudong]] Waigaiqiao Free-Trade Zone\n* [[Shanghai]] [[Pudong]] Jinqiao Export Manufacturing Zone\n* [[Shanghai]] [[Pudong]] [[Zhangjiang Hi-Tech Park]]\n* [[Hangzhou]]\n* [[Hangzhou]] [[Zhongshan|Xiangshan]]\n* [[Ningbo]]\n* [[Ningbo]] Daxie Island\n* [[Wenzhou]]\n* [[Fuzhou]] [[Mawei District]]\n* [[Xiamen]] [[Haicang District]]\n* [[Guangzhou]]\n* [[Guangzhou]] Nansha\n* [[Zhanjiang]]\n* [[Hainan]] [[Yangpu Economic Development Zone]]\n* [[Xining]]\n* [[Taiyuan]]\n* [[Lhasa|Lasa]]\n* [[Nanning]]\n* [[Lanzhou]]\n* [[Shuyang]] [[Shuyang Economic and Technological Development Zone]]\n\n==Provincial Economic Development Zones==\nThere are now many Provincial Economic Development Zones, such as:\n\n* [[Changxing Island (Dalian)#Dalian Changxing Island Seaport Industrial Area|Dalian Changxing Island Seaport Industrial Area]] ([[Liaoning]])\n* [[Dongying Economic Development Zone]] ([[Shandong]])\n* [[Yunmeng County]] Economic Development Zone, Xiaogan, Hubei\n* [[Hanchuan]] Economic and Technological Development Zone ({{lang|zh-hans|\u6c49\u5ddd\u5e02\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a}}),<ref name=\"xzqhhc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xzqh.org/html/show/hb/15392.html |script-title=zh:\u6c49\u5ddd\u5e02\u5386\u53f2\u6cbf\u9769|trans-title=Hanchuan City Historical Development| publisher=XZQH.org.org|quote=\"{{lang|zh-hans|\u6c49\u5ddd\u5e02\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a7647\u4eba\uff0c}}\"|date=6 August 2014|accessdate=28 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"statshc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.stats.gov.cn/tjsj/tjbz/tjyqhdmhcxhfdm/2016/42/09/420984.html |script-title=zh:2016\u5e74\u7edf\u8ba1\u7528\u533a\u5212\u4ee3\u7801\u548c\u57ce\u4e61\u5212\u5206\u4ee3\u7801\uff1a\u6c49\u5ddd\u5e02|trans-title=2016 Statistical Area Numbers and Rural-Urban Area Numbers: Hanchuan City |language=zh| publisher = [[National Bureau of Statistics of the People's Republic of China]] |quote=\"{{lang|zh-hans|420984504000 \u6c49\u5ddd\u5e02\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a}}\"|date=2016|accessdate=28 April 2018}}</ref> Xiaogan, Hubei\n* Jingzhou Economic and Technological Development Zone,<ref name=\"govjz\">{{cite web|url=http://jingzhou.gov.cn/z/zoujinjingzhou/ |script-title=zh:\u57ce\u5e02\u6982\u51b5 |trans-title=City Description | language = zh-hans|publisher=Jingzhou People's Government |quote={{lang|zh-hans|\u8346\u5dde\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a}}|date=|accessdate=11 June 2018}}</ref><ref>http://www.xzqh.org/html/show/hb/37311.html</ref> [[Jingzhou]], Hubei\n\nSome of them are as large as the National Economic and Technological Development Zones.  There are also the Municipal-Level Economic Development Zones.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Chinese economic reform]]\n* [[List of economic and technological development zones in Beijing]]\n* [[List of economic and technological development zones in Shanghai]]\n* [[List of technology centers|List of technology centers of the world]]\n* [[Megalopolises in China]]\n* [[Special economic zone]]\n* [[Special economic zones of China]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* <https://web.archive.org/web/20161220025544/http://www.ide.go.jp/English/Publish/Periodicals/De/pdf/87_01_05.pdf>\n* China Acadmenic Journals Full-text Database <http://www.eastview.com/>\n* <http://www.ntpu.edu.tw/econ/files/Journal/20110308170007.pdf>\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.mofcom.gov.cn/xglj/kaifaqu.shtml Ministry of Commerce (MOFCOM)]\n*[http://www.cadz.org.cn/ China Association of Development Zones]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20081221083440/http://www.export.gov/china/exporting_to_china/developmentzones.pdf China Development Zones]\n*[http://www.mainlandchinadevelopment.com/ Support service to enter development Zones to Mainland China]\n*[http://rightsite.asia/ China Industrial Zone and Property Directory at RightSite.asia]\n\n{{Economy of China}}\n{{SEZ}}\n\n[[Category:Economic development in China]]\n[[Category:Industry in China]]\n[[Category:Special Economic Zones of China|*]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Chinese\n|order = st\n|s = {{linktext|\u56fd\u5bb6|\u7ea7|\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a}}\n|t = \u570b\u5bb6\u7d1a\u7d93\u6fdf\u6280\u8853\u958b\u767c\u5340\n|p = Gu\u00f3ji\u0101j\u00ed J\u012bngj\u00ec J\u00ecsh\u00f9 K\u0101if\u0101 Q\u016b\n}}\n\nThe '''National Economic and Technological Development Zones''' ({{zh|s={{linktext|\u56fd\u5bb6|\u7ea7|\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a}}|t=\u570b\u5bb6\u7d1a\u7d93\u6fdf\u6280\u8853\u958b\u767c\u5340|p=Gu\u00f3ji\u0101j\u00ed J\u012bngj\u00ec J\u00ecsh\u00f9 K\u0101if\u0101 Q\u016b}}) are the special areas of the [[China|People's Republic of China]] where [[foreign direct investment]] is encouraged.  They are usually called the \"Economic and Technological Development Zones\" or simply the \"Development Zones\".\n\nThese national level programs started with the [[special economic zones of China|Special Economic Zones]] for three cities in 1978, as part of [[Chinese economic reform|China's economic reform]], and were extended to the Economic and Technological Development Zones in 14 cities in 1984.\n\nThere are also pros and cons on development on these economic zones, the pros are creating more job opportunities, increasing its economic growth (national GDP) and encourage on foreign direct investment. As a result, it was a success because China is currently one of the fastest growing countries and significantly influencing the global economy. From the past two decades, China has become an industrialized country because of the development of these economic zones. In which encourage foreign direct investments, where trading, exports of manufacture goods, became one of the main aspect of economic growth. On the other hand, it also made it reliant  on these foreign investment, such as reliant on Hong Kong for these foreign investment, due to the reason that Hong Kong is a free trade market. Based on the case in Shenzhen, its problem with being one of the economic zones can be categorized in four category 1) Foreign exchange leakage,2) Cost ineffectiveness, 3) Failure to achieve state objectives and 4) Economic crimes and related social problems.[https://web.archive.org/web/20161220025544/http://www.ide.go.jp/English/Publish/Periodicals/De/pdf/87_01_05.pdf]\n\nChina has been among the top targets of global investment for more than two decades.   In the new age of [[global recession]], China keeps a stable [[Economic growth|growth rate]], thanks to the inexpensive labor, stable government, preferable [[tax rate]] and government's support to [[foreign direct investment|foreign investment]].\n\n==List of zones==\nIn 2006, there are now 49 Development Zones (in the order of the list in the [[:zh:\u56fd\u5bb6\u7ea7\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a|Chinese Wikipedia page]], i.e. in the order of the approvals):\n\n* [[Dalian Development Area]]\n* [[Haining]]\n* [[Qinhuangdao]]\n* [[Tianjin Economic-Technological Development Area]]\n* [[Yantai]]\n* [[Qingdao]]\n* [[Nantong]]\n* [[Lianyungang]]\n* [[Weihai]]\n* [[Fuqing]] Rongqiao\n* [[Tongshan County, Hubei|Tongshan]]\n* [[Shenyang]]\n* [[Harbin]]\n* [[Changchun]]\n* [[Wuhan]]\n* [[Wuhu City|Wuhu]]\n* [[Huizhou]] Dayawan\n* [[Beijing]]\n* [[Urumuqi]]\n* [[Hefei]]\n* [[Zhengzhou]]\n* [[Xi'an]]\n* [[Chengdu]]\n* [[Kunming]]\n* [[Changsha Economic and Technological Development Zone]]\n* [[Guiyang]]\n* [[Nanchang]]\n* [[Hohhot]]\n* [[Yinchuan]]\n* [[Nanjing]]\n* [[Suzhou Industrial Park]]\n* [[Shanghai]] Minhang\n* [[Shanghai]] Hongqiao\n* [[Caohejing Development Zone (Shanghai Metro)|Shanghai Caohejing Development Zone (Shanghai Metro)]]\n* [[Shanghai]] [[Pudong]] [[Lujiazui|Lujiazui Financial & Trading Zone]]\n* [[Shanghai]] [[Pudong]] Waigaiqiao Free-Trade Zone\n* [[Shanghai]] [[Pudong]] Jinqiao Export Manufacturing Zone\n* [[Shanghai]] [[Pudong]] [[Zhangjiang Hi-Tech Park]]\n* [[Hangzhou]]\n* [[Hangzhou]] [[Zhongshan|Xiangshan]]\n* [[Ningbo]]\n* [[Ningbo]] Daxie Island\n* [[Wenzhou]]\n* [[Fuzhou]] [[Mawei District]]\n* [[Xiamen]] [[Haicang District]]\n* [[Guangzhou]]\n* [[Guangzhou]] Nansha\n* [[Zhanjiang]]\n* [[Hainan]] [[Yangpu Economic Development Zone]]\n* [[Xining]]\n* [[Taiyuan]]\n* [[Lhasa|Lasa]]\n* [[Nanning]]\n* [[Lanzhou]]\n* [[Shuyang]] [[Shuyang Economic and Technological Development Zone]]\n\n==Provincial Economic Development Zones==\nThere are now many Provincial Economic Development Zones, such as:\n\n* [[Changxing Island (Dalian)#Dalian Changxing Island Seaport Industrial Area|Dalian Changxing Island Seaport Industrial Area]] ([[Liaoning]])\n* [[Dongying Economic Development Zone]] ([[Shandong]])\n* [[Yunmeng County]] Economic Development Zone, Xiaogan, Hubei\n* [[Hanchuan]] Economic and Technological Development Zone ({{lang|zh-hans|\u6c49\u5ddd\u5e02\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a}}),<ref name=\"xzqhhc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.xzqh.org/html/show/hb/15392.html |script-title=zh:\u6c49\u5ddd\u5e02\u5386\u53f2\u6cbf\u9769|trans-title=Hanchuan City Historical Development| publisher=XZQH.org.org|quote=\"{{lang|zh-hans|\u6c49\u5ddd\u5e02\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a7647\u4eba\uff0c}}\"|date=6 August 2014|accessdate=28 April 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"statshc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.stats.gov.cn/tjsj/tjbz/tjyqhdmhcxhfdm/2016/42/09/420984.html |script-title=zh:2016\u5e74\u7edf\u8ba1\u7528\u533a\u5212\u4ee3\u7801\u548c\u57ce\u4e61\u5212\u5206\u4ee3\u7801\uff1a\u6c49\u5ddd\u5e02|trans-title=2016 Statistical Area Numbers and Rural-Urban Area Numbers: Hanchuan City |language=zh| publisher = [[National Bureau of Statistics of the People's Republic of China]] |quote=\"{{lang|zh-hans|420984504000 \u6c49\u5ddd\u5e02\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a}}\"|date=2016|accessdate=28 April 2018}}</ref> Xiaogan, Hubei\n* Jingzhou Economic and Technological Development Zone,<ref name=\"govjz\">{{cite web|url=http://jingzhou.gov.cn/z/zoujinjingzhou/ |script-title=zh:\u57ce\u5e02\u6982\u51b5 |trans-title=City Description | language = zh-hans|publisher=Jingzhou People's Government |quote={{lang|zh-hans|\u8346\u5dde\u7ecf\u6d4e\u6280\u672f\u5f00\u53d1\u533a}}|date=|accessdate=11 June 2018}}</ref><ref>http://www.xzq