06\n|[[Zamperla]]<br />Disk'O\n|Originally known as ''Survivor: The Ride!'' from 2006\u20132011.\n|bgcolor=\"#FF0000\" align=center | 4\n|}\n\n[[File:Ride at California's Great America.JPG|thumb|right|Delirium (a [[pendulum ride]])]]\n\n===All American Corners===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Ride\n!Opened\n!Manufacturer, type\n!Notes\n!Rating<ref name=Rating/>\n|-\n|[[Mass Effect: New Earth]]\n|2016\n|4-D Theater\n|Originally 'Action Theater' with several shows.\n|bgcolor=\"#FFA343\" align=center | 3\n|-\n|Delirium\n|2002\n|Chance Rides<br/>Revolution 32\n|Designed by [[KMG (company)|KMG]] of the Netherlands.\n|bgcolor=\"#800080\" align=center | {{fontcolor|white|5}}\n|-\n|Flying Eagles\n|2002\n|[[Larson International]]<br/>[[Flying Scooters]]\n|Cars can reach an overall height of 28 feet during ride operation.\n|bgcolor=\"#FFA343\" align=center | 3\n|-\n|Orbit\n|1976\n|Schwarzkopf<br/>[[Enterprise (ride)|Enterprise]]\n|Originally the ''Orleans Orbit''.\n|bgcolor=\"#FF0000\" align=center | 4\n|-\n|Rip Roaring Rapids\n|1988\n|[[Intamin]] [[river rafting ride]]\n|Riders careen through the concrete channels in 6-person rafts while facing rapids, whirlpools, and waterfalls.\n|bgcolor=\"#800080\" align=center | {{fontcolor|white|5}}\n|}\n\n===Celebration Plaza===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Ride\n!Opened\n!Manufacturer, type\n!Notes\n!Rating<ref name=Rating/>\n|-\n|[[Columbia Carousel|Carousel Columbia]]\n|1976\n|[[Chance Rides]]<br />Double Decker Carousel\n|A double-Decker carousel that has over 100 horses and stands an overall height of 101 feet tall.\n|bgcolor=\"#1ACDEA\" align=center | '''{{fontcolor|white|1}}'''\n|-\n|Celebration Swings\n|2001\n|[[Zierer]] [[Wave swinger]]\n|Originally operated at [[Carowinds]] as ''Whirling Dervish'' from 1979\u20132000.\n|bgcolor=\"#FED530\" align=center | '''{{fontcolor|white|3}}'''\n|-\n|[[Gold Striker]]\n|2013\n|[[Great Coasters International]]<br />[[Wooden roller coaster]]\n|Featured as a top 50 wooden roller